           <li>{{ city }}: {{ items|map(attribute="name")|join(", ") }}</li>
         {% endfor %}</ul>
 
+    Like the :func:`~jinja-filters.sort` filter, sorting and grouping is
+    case-insensitive by default. The ``key`` for each group will use the
+    case of the first item encountered for that value. For example, if a
+    list of items has cities ``["CA", "NY", "ca"]``, the ``"CA"`` and
+    ``"ca"`` entries will be grouped together, under a group named
+    ``"CA"``. This can be disabled by passing ``case_sensitive=True``.
+
+    .. sourcecode:: jinja
+
+        <ul>{% for city, items in users|groupby("city", case_sensitive=true) %}
+          <li>{{ city }}: {{ items|map(attribute="name")|join(", ") }}</li>
+        {% endfor %}</ul>
+
+    You can use ``include_empty=False`` to exclude groups where the
+    attribute is ``None``, an empty string, or another falsy value.
+
+    .. sourcecode:: jinja
+
+        <ul>{% for city, items in users|groupby("city", include_empty=false) %}
+          <li>{{ city }}: {{ items|map(attribute="name")|join(", ") }}</li>
+        {% endfor %}</ul>
+
+    .. versionchanged:: 3.1
+        Added the ``case_sensitive`` and ``include_empty`` parameters.
+
     .. versionchanged:: 3.0
         Added the ``default`` parameter.
 
